{"blocks":[{"key":"9gqb5","text":"Prepare dilution series: ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3ru68","text":"Probably, the concentration of the PCR products is way too high for qPCR. {"blocks":[{"key":"bto61","text":"Measure highest standard in QBIT (high sensitivity kit) and calculate concentration for dilutions (~ 1-5 ng/µl)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fg2h2","text":"calculate copy numbers http://cels.uri.edu/gsc/cndna.html ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":23,"length":34}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"C5659C360BE711EC806D0A58A9FEAC02","url":"http://cels.uri.edu/gsc/cndna.html"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"732t0","text":"Thaw tissue samples on ice and meanwhile label lysis tubes (label on the side, since during powerlysing step labelling on the lid might disappear!)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"evs1h","text":"Remove first sample from the cryovial (leave others on ice) and cut on a sterile petri dish with sterile forceps into pieces","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2sflm","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ais32","text":"Tare the lysis tube and load with ~80 mg tissue. Place tube on ice and proceed with the next sample (go back to step 4.2). Use a new petri dish and scalpel to prevent cross-contamination.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6hhmc","text":"Add 600 µl beta-mercaptoethanol/RTL buffer under the hood and disrupt cells in homogenizer for 30 sec at a speed of 3000","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"blscs","text":"Centrifuge for 10 min at maximum speed","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6labb","text":"Remove supernatant carefully without touching the pellet and transfer it to a 2 ml collection tube. From here on, work at RT","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cg3l0","text":"add 1 volume (~370 µl) of 70 % molecular grade ethanol and mix well by pipetting. Proceed immediately to next step","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"62ubl","text":"transfer up to 700 µl including any precipitate to RNeasy Spin column placed in a 2 ml collection tube (provided in kit). Close the lid and centrifuge for 30 sec at 10,000 rpm. Discard flow-through and re-use collection tube. Repeat this step if the sample exceeded 700 µl","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"3bknb","text":"Add 700 µl RW1 buffer and centrifuge for 30 sec at 10,000 rpm. Discard the flow-through","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aeti2","text":"Add 500 µl RPE buffer and centrifuge for 30 sec at 10,000 rmp. Discard the flow-through","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"f3dcp","text":"Add 500 µl RPE buffer and centrifuge for 2 min at 10,000 rpm. Carefully remove the spin column and place it in fresh 2 ml collection tube. Centrifuge for 1 min at max speed to remove any remaining buffer","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d2473","text":"Place the spin column in a fresh 1.5 ml Eppendorf tube and add 60 µl EB buffer. Take care to place it directly onto the spin column membrane. Close the lid and incubate for 10 min at RT. Centrifuge for 1 min at 10,000 rpm to elute RNA","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bg0ap","text":"Keep extracts always on ice! Proceed immediately with RNase inhibition and nuclease treatment.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2of70","text":"Already preheat incubator or heating block to 37°C (incubator needs much longer to pre-heat than heating block)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8ua8g","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2d1mk","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"e74hj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"safety","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":11,"offset":51,"style":"italic"},{"length":33,"offset":98,"style":"italic"},{"length":10,"offset":230,"style":"italic"},{"length":1,"offset":241,"style":"italic"}],"key":"64j09","text":"important! The DNase treatment was challenging for H. panicea extracts. For other sponge species (Aplysina aerophoba, Dysidea avara) we have successfully used the TURBO™ DNase (AM2238) kit for DNA removal, but it did not work for H. panicea: DNA remained and RNA was degraded, even if we tested different batches of the kit. We also tried unsuccessfully the on-column kit RNase-Free DNase Set (79254). ","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":13,"offset":9,"style":"bold"},{"length":11,"offset":99,"style":"italic"}],"key":"8bl06","text":"Finally, good results were obtained with the DNA-free™ DNA Removal Kit (AM1906) to remove DNA from H. panicea RNA extracts.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1hnud","text":"Under the clean bench: add 3 µl SUPERase-IN (0.05 volume of RNA) to 60 µl RNA. Mix gently","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ibbf","text":"Add 6 µl (0.1 volume of RNA) 10x DNAse I buffer and 1.2 µl DNAse and mix gently","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"7n5ca","text":"Incubate for 20 min at 37°C, mix frequently","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8dvom","text":"Add 6 µl resuspended DNAse I inactivation reagent and mix well","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8shjh","text":"Incubate for 2-5 min at RT, mix every minute by shortly vortexing","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1jvft","text":"Centrifuge for 1.5 min at 10,300 rpm and transfer supernatant (RNA) to a fresh tube. Take care to not transfer any inactivation reagent (white)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8ig4g","text":"We recommend to immediately take a 5 µl aliquot and a 2 µl aliquot, and freeze all samples at -80°C. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3diml","text":"Use the 5 µl aliquot to assess quality and quantity (Nanodrop, Qbit, PCR to check contamination with DNA) and the 2 µl aliquot for capillary electrophoresis (e.g. Experion). To avoid thaw-freeze cycles, the main RNA sample can be split in two equal parts, so that one sample can remain frozen until analysis at -80°C if it is intended for e.g. transcriptomics","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8vm27","text":"Extract DNA from bacterial recolonization pellets flash frozen (stored at -80°C)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":80}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"evfne","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5ladq","text":"Qiagen Blood+Tissue kit","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d066v","text":"Input: cell pellet","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8k2jm","text":"Process max.24 samples at a time, depending on experience","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3rs70","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bmbse","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"154bg","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"2mjc7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"843rf","text":"No good results were achieved with the Qiagen PowerSoil Kit for cell pellets.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"edka4","text":"Follow manufacturers protocol (incubation with proteinase K at 56°C for 30 min)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"8f0ql","text":"Store cDNA dilutions at -20°C","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"75ceu","text":"Dilute cDNA 1:5 with TE buffer and use this dilution for qPCR","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ce4s9","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"906j0","text":" Run plate immediately, or store plate at 4°C in the dark and run within 24 h","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"crvfd","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8rdb3","text":"     96°C      2 min               94°C      30 sec      40x        60°C      30 sec (plate read)        72°C      1 min (plate read)        60-90°C      0.5 interval, 5 sec Melt   curve          ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":196}],"data":{}},{"key":"1cars","text":" ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"tables","mutability":"","data":{"cellsMeta":{"0_0":"","0_1":"","0_2":"","1_0":"","1_1":"","1_2":"","2_0":"","2_1":"","3_0":"","3_1":"","4_0":"","4_1":"","4_2":""},"colTitles":["","",""],"colWidths":["67","192","34"],"data":[["  72°C  ","  1 min (plate read)  ",""],["  96°C  ","  2 min  ","40x"],["  94°C  ","  30 sec  ",""],["  60°C  ","  30 sec (plate read)  ",""],["  60-90°C  ","  0.5 interval, 5 sec Melt curve  ","     "]],"guid":"8010A573275311ECA22E0A58A9FEAC02","isJexcelDataFormat":true,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"fru2b","text":"Table: qPCR conditions","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mergeCells":{"C_2":[1,3]},"printData":[["  72°C  ","  1 min (plate read)  ",""],["  96°C  ","  2 min  ","40x"],["  94°C  ","  30 sec  ",""],["  60°C  ","  30 sec (plate read)  ",""],["  60-90°C  ","  0.5 interval, 5 sec Melt curve  ","     "]],"rowHeights":[23,23,23,23,23]}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"c878a","text":"Work in 96-well plate. Pipet 15 µl master mix per well","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"60c87","text":"Add 5 µl template per well (use new pipet tip for each well)","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"77kd6","text":"Seal plate with optical adhesive foil (check which brand fits your plates and qPCR machine) and spin down plate briefly in plate centrifuge","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b7vfv","text":"Run gel electrophoresis with some qPCR products to check for correct amplification (1 band of correct product length) at least once per experiment","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
